Chilean Stocks: CCU, Cencosud, Lan Airlines, SQM and Vapores

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-08-08T21:14:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/chilean-stocks-ccu-cencosud-lan-airlines-sqm-and-vapores.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:16 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index dropped 6.9 percent to 3,784.65, its biggest
fall in almost 13 years. The index has fallen 25 percent since
its Jan. 6 high of 5,048.13, reaching a  bear market , typically
defined as a drop of at least 20 percent from the preceding
bull-market peak.  Cia. Cervecerias Unidas SA (CCU CC) fell 2.1 percent to
4,846.6 pesos, its ninth decline in 10 sessions. Chile’s largest
brewer had its recommendation cut to “underperform” from
“neutral” at Credit Suisse AG by analyst Antonio Gonzalez.  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD CC),  Latin America ’s third-largest
retailer by sales, slid 8.3 percent to 2,500.80 pesos, the
biggest fall since October 2008. Chilean stocks overall declined
in line with the slump in U.S. stocks today,  Cesar Perez , a
managing director at Santiago-based brokerage Celfin Capital SA,
said in a telephone interview today.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)  , Latin America’s largest airline
by market value, declined 7.7 percent 10,429 pesos.  Cia
Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES)   dropped a record 16
percent to 205.44 pesos.  Soc. Quimica y Minera de Chile SA (SQM/B CC) plunged 7.1
percent to 24,594 pesos, its fifth day of losses. Chile’s
largest fertilizer producer fell in line with agricultural
commodity prices, which signals lower demand for its products.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
